Hey i can do that in $php too!<p><pre><code>    function execute($order, $callbacks){
        foreach($order as $i){
            $callbacks[$i]();
        }
    }

    function abcProcs(){
        foreach(func_get_args() as $f){
            eval(&quot;function $f() { echo &#x27;$f&#x27;; };&quot;);
        }
    }

    abcProcs(&quot;A&quot;,&quot;B&quot;,&quot;C&quot;);
    execute([0,0,1,2,1,2], [&#x27;A&#x27;,&#x27;B&#x27;,&#x27;C&#x27;]);
</code></pre>
edit:<p>you don&#x27;t have to quote the function names (just to show they are really functions and not closures):<p><pre><code>    execute([0,0,1,2,1,2], [A,B,C]);</code></pre>
